      <h1 class='title'>Retail Pharmacy Services</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 27 October 2003 vol 412 cc20-1WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_20ws' title='Col. 20WS &mdash; HC Deb 27 October 2003 vol 412 c20WS' name='column_20ws' href='#column_20ws' rel='bookmark'>20WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S6CV0412P0-04553'>
        <a name='S6CV0412P0_20031027_CWS2_101'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-john-cryer' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0412P0_20031027_CWS2_101' title='Link to this speech by Mr John Cryer' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-john-cryer" title="Mr John Cryer">John Cryer</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S6CV0412P0-04553">To ask the Secretary of State for Trade and Industry whether the proposed exemption of large shopping developments from the control of entry requirements for retail pharmacy services will be restricted to bespoke shopping developments. [133276]</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S6CV0412P0-04554'>
        <a name='S6CV0412P0_20031027_CWS2_102'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/ms-rosie-winterton' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0412P0_20031027_CWS2_102' title='Link to this speech by Ms Rosie Winterton' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/ms-rosie-winterton" title="Ms Rosie Winterton">Ms Rosie Winterton</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S6CV0412P0-04554">I have been asked to reply.</p><p id="S6CV0412P0-04555">As part of the balanced package of measures, announced on 17 July 2003, the Government proposed that shopping developments over 15,000 square metres would be exempt from the control of entry requirements for national health service pharmaceutical services. Such developments include purpose-built named shopping developments in town centres, on edge-of-centre and out-of-centre sites, major regional shopping
          
          <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_21ws' title='Col. 21WS &mdash; HC Deb 27 October 2003 vol 412 c21WS' name='column_21ws' href='#column_21ws' rel='bookmark'>21WS</a>
          centres, retail warehouse parks and factory outlet centres. We are currently consulting on these proposals and would welcome views</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
